 Bellair SAPS CPF chairperson, Malcolm Naidoo, called on residents to bring their children as there are a host of fun activities for the whole family. 

 

 "We have stalls, competitions and entertainment for all ages. We are looking forward to this event and know this will be the first of many," Naidoo said. 

 

 The Crime Awareness Day is set to start at 8am on August 18 at the Hillary Primary School. 

 

